As a tribute to her mother, Ms Lafferty wore custom sneakers as part of her bridal ensemble.

‘My mom always teased me because I was such a tomboy," she told People.

‘When I was picking out my dress, we found you could custom Converse sneakers, so she knew I had ordered them.’

The recently-married Ms Lafferty also shared that she finds a way to keep her mother part of every single day. Just days before the wedding, she posted a picture of a sign she left at her mother’s grave.

Mr Smegielski stood by Ms Lafferty during a number of interviews immediately following the December 14 tragedy.

In a segment for The Today Show, he said: 'For some reason Dawn loved me and it's my job now to be there for her daughter'.

